MatchLocate2.c
It's the main code to detect and locate small events.

MatchLocate2.1.c
It's the main code to detect and locate small events (with an option for bandpass fitering).

SelectFinal.c
If you have lots of templates, one event might be detected more than once.
Now, you should use this code to choose one best among them.

SHIFT.c [for plotting only]
Get time shift between the detected event and the reference event at one station.
You may need it when you plot the seismogram comparision.

sacCC [for plotting only]
compute the normalized cross-correlation.

lsac [for plotting only]
get the amplitude at one point in SAC file. [From Lupei Zhu's code]
